      <body>
         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="left">
               <hi rend="print">
                  <orgName type="firm" ref="K01071">JOH. BERENBERG, GOSSLER &amp;
                            CO.</orgName>
                  <lb/>
                  <placeName ref="K00522">HAMBURG</placeName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <seg rend="right">
               <hi rend="latintype">
                  <placeName ref="K00522">Hamburg</placeName>
                  <date when="1871-07-13">13 July 1871</date>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <hi rend="latintype">via <placeName ref="K00554">Brindisi</placeName>
            </hi>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="center">Herren <hi rend="latintype">
                  <orgName type="firm" ref="K01004">L. Kniffler &amp; C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
                  </orgName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/>
            <seg rend="right">
               <hi rend="latintype">
                  <placeName ref="K00525">Yokohama</placeName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
            <lb/> Wir nehmen höflich Bezug an<lb/> unser Ergebenes v. <date when="1871-05-19">19
                        <hi rend="latintype">May,</hi>
            </date> dessen Abschrift wir<lb/> beifügen.<lb/> Auf Wunsch der Herren<lb/>
            <hi rend="latintype">
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01034">L. E. Amsinck &amp; C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
               </orgName>
            </hi> in <hi rend="latintype">
               <placeName ref="K00531">New-York</placeName>
            </hi> bestätigen wir<lb/> Ihnen daß dieselben einen Credit zu Ihren Gunsten<lb/> für
                    <hi rend="underline">
               <term type="commercial" ref="K01522">£</term>
               <measure type="currency" unit="britPound" quantity="5000">5000.-</measure>
            </hi> (<hi rend="latintype">
               <measure type="currency" unit="britPound" quantity="5000">Fünftausend</measure>
               <term type="measure" ref="K01522">Pfund Sterling</term>
            </hi>)<lb/> bei uns eröffnet haben, zu benutzen entweder<lb/> durch Ihre <term type="commercial" ref="K01534">Tratten</term> oder durch diejenigen Ihrer
                Häuser<lb/> in <hi rend="latintype">
               <placeName ref="K00545">Hiogo</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="K00514">Nagasaki</placeName>
            </hi>, 4 oder 6 Monate nach Sicht<lb/> auf uns direct, oder auf uns zahlbar bei der
                    <hi rend="latintype">
               <orgName type="firm" ref="K01072">Union<lb/> Bank of London</orgName>
            </hi>, als Vorschuß von 7,5% auf <term type="logistic" ref="K01584">Con-<lb/>
                    signationen</term> an die Adresse genannter <hi rend="latintype">
               <placeName ref="K00531">New-York</placeName>
            </hi>
            <lb/> Freunde. Der Advis solcher <term type="commercial" ref="K01534">Tratten</term>
                ist von Ver-<lb/> schiffungsdocumenten zu begleiten, und bleibt<lb/> dieser Credit
                bis zum <date when="1872-03-01">1 <hi rend="latintype">März</hi> 1872</date> dort in Kraft.<lb/>
            <add style="transformRotateZ(-45deg)" resp="unclear" place="marginLeft">
               <hi rend="underline">Copie<lb/>Bericht</hi>
            </add>
            <seg rend="right">Achtungsvoll &amp; Ergebenst<lb/>
               <hi rend="latintype">
                  <orgName type="firm" ref="K01071">JohBerenberg, GosslerC<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
                  </orgName>
               </hi>
            </seg>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_4.tif" n="4"/>
         <p>
            <seg rend="right">
               <add style="textOrientation: straight" resp="other">1871<lb/>
                  <hi rend="latintype">
                     <placeName ref="K00522">Hamburg</placeName>
                     <date when="1871-07-13">13 July</date>
                     <lb/>
                     <orgName type="firm" ref="K01071">J. Behrenberg,
                            Gossler+Co</orgName>,<lb/> R<hi rend="underline">
                        <date when="1871-08-27">27 Aug.</date>
                     </hi>
                     <lb/>
                     <date when="1871-09-04">4 Septbr</date>
                  </hi>
               </add>
            </seg>
         </p>
         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_5.tif" n="5"/>
         <p>
            <hi rend="print">
               <seg rend="right">
                  <placeName ref="K00522">Hamburg</placeName>, <date when="1871-01-24">January
                                24<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1871</date>.</seg>
               <lb/>
               <seg rend="center">
                  <orgName type="firm" ref="K01071">John Berenberg, Gossler &amp; C<hi rend="superscript">o</hi>
                  </orgName>.</seg>
               <lb/> The weather remains mild, steamers reach <placeName ref="K00601">Glückstadt</placeName> easily, while sailing vessels go to <placeName ref="K00602">Cuxhaven</placeName>.<lb/> Our Colonial and Foreign Produce
                    markets have been quiet at about last prices. <term type="goods" ref="K01822">COFFEE</term> firm with reduced stocks. <term type="goods" ref="K01559">COTTON</term>
               <lb/> the small remaining lts move off at comparatively high prices. <term type="goods" ref="K01636">SUGAR</term> quiet at last rate. MONEY is freely
                    offered at 3½ to 4% for<lb/> Discounts, 5 to 6% for Loans on Stocks an Shares.
                    U. S. 5/20 Bonds of 1862 89⅞%. Exchange 3 ₻ pr. $.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01823">COCOA</term> steady but without sales of moment.
                    We quote: <placeName ref="K00603">Guayaquil</placeName> 4 ¾ - 5½ ß, <placeName ref="K00604">Pará</placeName> 6 ß, <placeName ref="K00605">Bahia</placeName>
                    4¼ ß; <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> 4 ß, <placeName ref="K00607">Caracas</placeName> 10½ - 11 ß<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01822">COFFEE</term>. The market continues quite firm
                    and afloat a large business has been done also for this week at full and rather
                    somewhat<lb/> improving prices. <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName>
                    received continued attention and of the lots mentioned as sold sundry resales
                    were made, which however<lb/> we do not specify. Sales are:<lb/>
               <table>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>4000</cell>
                     <cell>Bags</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00587">Rio</placeName> &amp; <placeName ref="K00618">Santos</placeName> on spot,</cell>
                     <cell/>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>&amp; afloat:</cell>
                     <cell>4754</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00587">Rio</placeName> pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01847">Dante</name>” at 5 5/16 ß </cell>
                     <cell rows="2">landed terms,</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>4540</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>＂ ＂ “<name type="ship" ref="K01848">Anna Maria</name>” at 5 5/16 ß</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>3687</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00618">Santos</placeName> pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01850">Canadia</name>” at 5 11/16 ß</cell>
                     <cell>do</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>3000</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>＂ ＂ “<name type="ship" ref="K01851">Schön</name>” at secret prices,</cell>
                     <cell/>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>2300</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01852">Sky Pelham</name>” from
                                    <placeName ref="K00531">New York</placeName>
                     </cell>
                     <cell rows="3">
                        <lb/>at 5¼ - 5½ ß.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>1500</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>＂ ＂ Str. “<name type="ship" ref="K01853">Cimbria</name>” do.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell/>
                     <cell>1000</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>＂ ＂ Steamer ＂ do.</cell>
                  </row>
               </table>
               <lb/> We quote: <placeName ref="K00587">Rio</placeName> inferior &amp; ord. 5⅛ - 5 5/16 ß, good. reg. 5⅜ - 5½ ß,
                    good first 5 9/16 - 5⅝ ß, superior 5¾ - 6 ß, <placeName ref="K00618">Santos</placeName> ord. 5⅛ - 5 5/16 ß,<lb/>
                    regular 6⅜ - 5 9/16 ß, <placeName ref="K00634">Campinas</placeName> 5⅝ - 6¼ ß, Laguayra trilladoes 5½ - 6¼
                    descerezadoes 6 - 7⅝ ß, <placeName ref="K00629">Maracaibo</placeName> 5¼ - 7½ ß, Portorico 6 - 7¾ ß,<lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> inferior 5 3/16 - 5½ ß, Genaives
                    &amp; Cape 5⅝ - 6¼ ß.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01559">COTTON</term>. On spot high prices are paid for
                    the small lots offering and the stock left is quite trifling. Sales are:<lb/>
               <table>
                  <row>
                     <cell>1300</cell>
                     <cell>Bales</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00619">Barcelona</placeName> at 8½ - 8¼ ß,</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>1400</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00618">Santos</placeName> at 8⅞ - 9 ß,</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>150</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>American at 8⅞ - 9 ß.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>300</cell>
                     <cell>＂</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00620">Valles</placeName> at 8¾.</cell>
                  </row>
               </table> Our quotations are: <term type="commercial" ref="K01723">Middling</term> New <term type="goods" ref="K01629">Orleans</term> 8½ ß,
                        <term type="commercial" ref="K01723">mid.</term>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01563">Uplands</term> 8¼ ß, fair <placeName ref="K00625">Bengal</placeName> 6¼ ß, fair
                    Dhollerah 6½ ß, fair Broach 6½ ß,<lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00621">Laguayra</placeName>
               <placeName ref="K00620">Valles</placeName> 7¼ - 7⅜ ß, <placeName ref="K00619">Barcelona</placeName> 8 -
                    8¼ ß, <placeName ref="K00622">Maroim</placeName> 8⅛ - 8¼ ß, prime <placeName ref="K00618">Santos</placeName> 8¼ - 8⅜ ß, prime Pernambs 8½ - 8⅝ ß, prime
                    <placeName ref="K00623">Ceará</placeName>
               <lb/> 8⅜ - 8½ ß, prime <placeName ref="K00624">Maceio</placeName> 8⅜ ß.<lb/> In <term type="goods" ref="K01526">DRUGS</term> &amp; <term type="goods" ref="K01824">DYES</term> a small
                    business. We quote: <hi rend="latintype">E. I. <term type="goods" ref="K01682">Saltpetre</term>
               </hi> flat at 13₻ pr. 93% refr. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01825">Nitrate of Soda</term>
               </hi> quiet, on<lb/> spot 11₻ afloat we quote 10₻. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01821">Gambier</term>
               </hi> worth 11₻ 4 ß. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01826">Turmeric</term>
               </hi> 15 ₻. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01827">Cutch</term>
               </hi> dull and lower not<lb/> worth above 14½ ₻. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01591">Staranisseed-Oil</term>
               </hi> lower and not worth above 6 ₻ 10 ß. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01591">Cassia-Oil</term>
               </hi> 3 ₻ 2ß. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01828">Shellac</term>
               </hi> firm, we quote<lb/> D C 12½ ß, M S 11½ ß, <term type="goods" ref="K01854">Garnet</term> 10 ß, Bloodlac 7½ - 11½
                    ß, Native sorts 9½ - 10 ß, but no Stock. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01855">India
                        Rubber</term>
               </hi> firm at<lb/> 42 ß for <placeName ref="K00604">Pará</placeName>,
                    wet <placeName ref="K00603">Guayaquil</placeName> 17 ß, <placeName ref="K00623">Ceara</placeName> 20 - 20½ ß. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01633">Indigo</term>
               </hi> remains neglected, prime <placeName ref="K00625">Bengal</placeName> 7 - 7¾ ₻,
                    medium 5⅞ - 6¼ ₻,<lb/> common 4⅛ - 5½ ₻, <placeName ref="K00626">Guatemala</placeName> prime 4¾ - 5¼ ₻, medium 4 -
                    4¼ ₻, common 3 - 3¼ ₻.<lb/> DYEWOODS are firm in particular <term type="goods" ref="K01860">Logwood</term>. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01860">Logwood</term>
               </hi>
               <placeName ref="K00627">Laguna Campeachy</placeName> 7 ₻, <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> 3 ₻ 3 ₻ 4 ß, <placeName ref="K00628">Jamaica</placeName> 380 Tons sold<lb/> to arrive, we
                    quote 3 ₻ 2 - 6 ß, <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01856">Fustic</term>
               </hi> inactive, <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> 3 ₻ 8 ß, <placeName ref="K00629">Maracaibo</placeName> 3 ₻ 4 ß, Laguna 4 ₻ 4 ß,
                    <placeName ref="K00630">Savanilla</placeName> 3 ₻,<lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00631">Curacao</placeName> 3 ₻ 4 ß, St. Martha 3 ₻. <placeName ref="K00637">Cuba</placeName> 5 ₻, <placeName ref="K00638">Porto Cabello</placeName> 3 ₻
                    4 ß - 4 ₻. - <hi rend="latintype">Redwood</hi>
               <placeName ref="K00636">Altata</placeName> 6 ₻. - <placeName ref="K00596">Lima</placeName> 5 ₻ 8 ß - 5 ₻ 12 ß.<lb/> - Extract of <term type="goods" ref="K01860">Logwood</term>
                    Sanford brand 4⅛ ß. - <hi rend="latintype">Quercitron Bark</hi>
               <placeName ref="K00640">Philadelphia</placeName> 6
                    ₻, <placeName ref="K00639">Baltimore</placeName> 4¼ - 4½ ₻.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01861">HIDES</term>. Continue firm for all sorts. Sales are:<lb/>
               <table>
                  <row>
                     <cell>5657</cell>
                     <cell>wet salted</cell>
                     <cell>
                        <placeName ref="K00641">Rio Grande</placeName> Ox </cell>
                     <cell>pr. “<name type="ship" ref="1859">E. Klosterhow,</name>”</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>3153</cell>
                     <cell>do.</cell>
                     <cell>do. ＂ </cell>
                     <cell>＂ “<name type="ship" ref="K01862">Ane</name>” at 5⅝ ß,</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>2032</cell>
                     <cell>do.</cell>
                     <cell>do. Horse</cell>
                     <cell> ＂ do. at abt. 8 ₻ 4 ß,</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>776</cell>
                     <cell>dry</cell>
                     <cell>do. Ox</cell>
                     <cell> ＂ ＂ do.</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>4823</cell>
                     <cell>wet salted <placeName ref="K00642">Montevideo</placeName>
                     </cell>
                     <cell>pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01863">Hilkelina</name>,”</cell>
                  </row>
                  <row>
                     <cell>2550</cell>
                     <cell>dry <placeName ref="K00643">Angostura</placeName>
                     </cell>
                     <cell>pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01687">Flora</name>”</cell>
                  </row>
               </table>
               <lb/> We quote: <placeName ref="K00644">River Plate</placeName> wet salted 5½ - ⅝ ß, Cow 5½ - 5⅝ ß, heavy dry 9 - 10
                    ß, Rio Grande wet salted heavy Ox 5⅝ ß, Cow 5⅝ ß,<lb/> heavy dry 9⅜ -
                        9<unclear>⅜</unclear> ß, light dry 9½ ß, Pernambs dry salted 7¼ - 7½ ß, wet
                    salted 5 5⅛ ß, <placeName ref="K00605">Bahia</placeName> dry 8⅝ - 8¾ ß, dry salted 7 - 7¼ ß,<lb/>
               <placeName ref="K00623">Ceara</placeName> dry salted
                    7⅝ - 7⅞ ß, heavy <placeName ref="K00587">Rio de Janeiro</placeName> wet salted
                    Ox 5¼ ß, Cow 5¼ ß, <placeName ref="K00635">Laguayra</placeName> dry 8½ - 8¾ ß, East India Kips slaughtered,<lb/> 8 -
                    8½ ß, dead 7 ß, rejections 4¾ - 5¼ ß, as per weight &amp; quality.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01864">HONEY</term>
                    unchanged in value. We quote: 22 ₻ for <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName>, 24 ₻ for <placeName ref="K00637">Cuba</placeName>.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01541">BEESWAX</term> in better demand. We quote:
                    <placeName ref="K00606">Domingo</placeName> 16½ ß, Benguella 17½ ß, <placeName ref="K00645">Angola</placeName>
                    17 ß, Chili 18½ ß, Danish 17½ ß, American 16½ ß<lb/> to 16¾ ß, Swedish 17
                    ß.<lb/> In METALS no business transacted. <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01696">Copper</term>
               </hi>
                    steady, we quote <placeName ref="K00647">Chili</placeName> refined 46 ₻ 12 ß net, Norwegian 46 ₻ 8 ß net, <placeName ref="K00646">Kapunda</placeName>
                    imitation<lb/> 47 ₻ net, English cakes 47 ₻ net. - <hi rend="latintype">
                  <term type="goods" ref="K01772">Lead</term>
               </hi> quiet, Spanish, we quote soft 12 ₻. - <hi rend="latintype">Spelter</hi> inactive, we quote on spot 11 ₻ 12 ß.<lb/> NAVAL STORES are
                    firm. <hi rend="latintype">Spirits of Turpentine</hi> no stock left prices
                    nominal. - American 30 ₻, French 30 ₻. - <hi rend="latintype">Rosin</hi>
                    slightly<lb/> higher. Americ. darc brown 4 ₻ 4 ß, Strained 4½ ₻, white 4¾ - 6 ₻,
                    French 4¾ - 6 ₻<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01865">PETROLEUM</term> inactive partly in expectation of a soon reopened
                    navigation. Deliveries this week <measure type="volume" unit="barrels" quantity="2800" commodity="petroleum">2800</measure>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>Brls.</abbr>
                  <expan>Barrels</expan>
               </choice> Stock <measure type="volume" quantity="13262" commodity="petroleum" unit="13262">13,262</measure>
               <choice>
                  <abbr>Brls</abbr>
                  <expan>Barrels</expan>
               </choice>.<lb/> We quote:
                    prime white 14 ₻ 14 ß, standard white 14 ₻ 6 ß, January 14 ₻ 8 ß´, February 14 ₻
                    4 ß.<lb/>
               <term type="goods" ref="K01502">RICE</term> stationary in value<lb/>
               <seg rend="center">5200 Bags Java pr. “<name type="ship" ref="K01867">Sparkling Dew</name>,” at secret terms to
