         <pb facs="1871_07_13_Kniffler_Yokohama_von_Behrenberg_Gossler_Co_Hamburg_1.tif" n="1"/>
         <p>JOH. BEHRENBER, GOSSLER &amp; CO.<lb/>HAMBURG<lb/> Hamburg, 13th July 1871<lb/>via
                Brindisi<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp; Co.<lb/>Yokohama<lb/>We politely refer to our
                esteemed<lb/>letter from 19th May, a copy of which <lb/>we enclose.<lb/>At the
                request of Messrs. <lb/>L. E. Amsinck &amp; Co. in New York we confirm to you
                <lb/>that these gentlemen have with us opened a credit <lb/>of £5,000.- (five
                thousand pounds Sterling) <lb/>in your favour, to be used either through <lb/>your
                bills of exchange or those of your houses <lb/>in Hiogo &amp; Nagasaki, with a 4 or
                6 month view <lb/>to us directly, or payable to us at the Union<lb/> Bank of London,
                as an advance of 7.5% on<lb/>consignments to the address of said New
                York<lb/>friends. The notification of such bills of exchange<lb/>has to be
                accompanied by shipping documents, and <lb/>this credit will remain in force there
                until 1st March 1872. <lb/>⟨Copy<lb/>Report⟩<lb/> Yours sincerely &amp; respectfully
                <lb/> Joh Berenberg, Gossler Co.</p>
